pearl /pɜːl/

(pearls) 

1. N-COUNT A pearl is a hard round object that is shiny and creamy white in colour. Pearls grow inside the shell of an oyster and are used for making expensive jewellery. 珍珠 

例： She wore a string of pearls at her throat. 她那时脖子上带着一串珍珠。 

2. ADJ Pearl is used to describe something that looks like a pearl. 珍珠般的 

例： ...tiny pearl buttons. …珍珠般的小扣子 

3. ADJ of, made of, or set with pearl or mother-of-pearl 珍珠的; 贝母的; 镶珠的 

4. V to set with or as if with pearls 用珍珠镶嵌; 仿珍珠镶嵌

